solution.p:
For monotonicity, we look at the signs of the increments.
We find the zeros k^2-90k+1600 = 0 and then test the signs in intervals.
The equation is quadratic, so we can use the quadratic formula.

  k &= \frac{90 \pm \sqrt{(-90)^2 - 4(1)(1600)}}{2}
   &= \frac{90 \pm \sqrt{8100 - 6400}}{2}
   &= \frac{90 \pm \sqrt{8100 - 6400}}{2}
   &= \frac{90}{2} \pm \frac{\sqrt{1700}}{2}
   &= 45 \pm 5\sqrt{17}

In this case, the exact values are not as useful as the approximate decimal values.
k \approx 24.38 \quad \text{or} \quad k \approx 65.62

